Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Heat the @oil{1%tbsp}(for cooking) in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and onion to the pan and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the chicken is golden all over and the onion is softened,
~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} to the water and cook until tender,
~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Once the chicken is golden, add the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if
you'd prefer things milder), garlic and @coleslaw mix{120%g} to the pan. Fry for
~{1%minute}.

Stir the @mango chutney{40%g}, @bulgogi sauce{75%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml},
@tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and @water{100%ml}(for the sauce) into the chicken pan.

Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked
through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

When the noodles are ready, stir them into the sauce until well combined.

Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it.

Share the mango chicken noodles between your #serving bowls{}.

Enjoy!